§ Definition ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $W$ be a positive semidefinite $n$ by $n$ matrix. ⦉

  ‖ Then $g: 𝗥^n → 𝗥$ defined by $g(x) = √{x^⊤ W x}$ is a
    norm on $𝗥^n$. ⦉
</statement>

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $W ∈ 𝗥^{n ×n}$, positive semidefinite. ⦉

  ‖ Then we denote the norm corresponding to $W$ by
    $\norm{·}_{W}$. ⦉

  ‖ So then, the norm of a vector $x ∈ 𝗥^n$ is $\norm{x}_{w}$. ⦉

  ‖ Notice that $\norm{x}_{W} = \norm{W^{1/2}x}_2$. ⦉
⦉

